              <img class="mb-4" src="images/logo150.png" width="100"><h6>Update 4/10/2020</h6>
              <p>Dear Parents, Students, and Staff of the Roberto Clemente Charter School,</p>
              <p>On April 9, 2020, Governor Wolf ordered all K-12 schools and programs,
                public and private, to be closed through the end of the 2019-2020 academic
                year. Pennsylvania Pre-K Counts, Head Start Supplemental Assistance
                Programs and Preschool Early Intervention programs will also remain closed,
                and institutions of higher education are prohibited from offering in-person
                instruction.</p>
                <p>All of these decisions were made in consultation with the Secretary of
                  Health, based on the most recent information regarding COVID-19 as it
                  relates to the health, safety, and welfare of students, school staff, and
                  communities.</p>
                  <p>Our elementary and middle/high school will continue with our plan of
                    education for the remainder of the academic year with the goal of keeping
                    our students connected and learning while they stay safe at home.</p>
                    <p>We will give special attention to our graduating class of 2020! Seniors
                      will begin a digital “planned instruction program” on Monday, April 13,
                      2020. This program will give them a feel for distant/online learning while
                      completing and earning their high school diplomas from the Roberto Clemente
                      Charter School.</p>
                      <p>I recognize that this may create some inconvenience to members of our
                        school community and we would like to keep an open line of communication
                        with our parents, students and staff.</p>
                        <p>Please let us know if we can be of any assistance to you with the
                          challenges of this pandemic. Also, please feel free to contact me or our
                          Principals with any ideas that may help us to improve our educational
                          processes.</p>
                          <p>Sincerely,</p>
                          <h6 class="pb-md-4">Jose Molina<br><br> Chief Executive Officer</h6>
              <h6>Update 4/3/2020</h6>
              <p>CONTINUATION OF EDUCATION PLANS POSTED: <a class="pl-2" href="middleandhighschool.html">MIDDLE/HIGH SCHOOL</a> <a class="pl-2" href="docs/RCECS%20Continuity%20of%20Education%20Plan%20March%2030,%202020.pdf" target="_blank">ELEMENTARY SCHOOL</a></p>
