<h6 class="pb-3">Dear Roberto Clemente Charter School Family,</h6>
                <p class="px-md-4">Today, March 13, 2020, Governor Tom Wolf announced that all K-12 Pennsylvania schools will be closed for 10 business days, effective Monday, March 16, 2020. The Commonwealth has been working with all schools across the state as well as Federal, state and local officials to gather input on this decision. The Wolf Administration will continue to monitor the Covid-19 situation in the commonwealth, and at the end of 10 days will reevaluate and decide whether continued closures are needed.  Please continue to check our school’s website for important information and updates during this time.</p>
